    Class Description
    AnimationData
    Contains all of the data required for the engine to use an animation.
    Barricade
    Barricades are objects that stand on the path to the end goal.
    Button
    This is a basic button that can be pressed or not pressed.
    Character
    Characters are GameObjects that represent living beings.
    CooldownTimer
    CooldownTimer represents a timer that counts down from a certain number of seconds to zero.
    Destructible
    Destructibles are GameObjects that can be destroyed.
    EffectVisual
    A visual effect.
    GameObjectPlus
    This class simply extends GameObject with some additional functionality.
    Grid
    The Grid is a 2-dimensional grid of Tiles.
    HTL
    Extend this class and override initializeWorld() and updateWorld() to make a game.
    JarResources  
    Path
    Paths are a spawn location followed by a series of Waypoints that ultimately lead to a final destination.
    Projectile
    A projectile is an object that is thrown by a Character.
    SetOfTowers
    This creates an interface for user interactions with a list of Towers.
    SetOfWalkers
    A whole list of Walkers, and some interfaces to easily interact with them.
    Smoke
    Smoke teleports characters and is characterized by its poofiness.
    StatusBar
    Status bars were used in the menu to display Towers' health and badFeels.
    StatusBarBadFeels
    Status bar representing a Tower's badFeels Hasn't been used in forever, and may be out of date.
    StatusBarHealth
    Status bar representing a Tower's health Hasn't been used in forever, and may be out of date.
    Tile
    A tile is a rectangular area representing terrain on a 2-dimensional grid.
    Tower
    Towers are meant to sit somewhere and shoot things in various ways.
    TowerMedic
    This tower is a medic, which means that it has the ability to heal things.
    TowerSpeedy
    This tower is speedy, which means that it has the ability to speed up things.
    Walker
    Walkers are the characters that move along the path.
    WalkerBasic
    This Walker is SO basic.
    WalkerQuick
    This Walker moves twice as fast as the Basic Walker, but has half the health.
    Wave
    A Wave is a series of Walkers that appears at a set rate during a level.
    WaveSystem
    The wave system is used to spawn waves of enemies in this game.
    Waypoint
    Waypoints are locations on the grid, and can be used to create a path.
